Harold Lopez-Nussa - Sobre El Atelier
2007

Cuban Music Series. The New Generation.

* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *

Harold was born in a family of musicians in Cuba: he is the nephew of the famous pianist Ernan Lopez Nussa and the son of the drummer Ruy Lopez Nussa.

This 24 years old pianist  profits, like all the members of his family, of a double upbringing, Cuban and French through his grand mother. Harold is now finishing his musical education at the Instituto Superior de Arte after a solid classical basis obtained at the Amadeo Roldan academy of music. In Cuba he is the winner of many classical piano contests, presents himself as a soloist in all the theatres of the island . Rapidly Harold opened up to traditional and popular music as well as jazz and started to play with the best musicians of the Island.  And now he focuses on jazz, his true passion.

He is laureate in 2005 of the Montreux Jazz Piano cometition and from there is performing in clubs of La Habana and outside of  the island in famous jazz festivals such as  Montreux, Vienna , Orleans, Verona, Festival de piano in EnghienÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚Â¦

